            "project": "al-futuro ",
            "section": 1,
            "title": "Al Futuro",
            "titleEn": "Al Futuro",
            "director": "Paz Fábrega",
            "producer": "Pamela Guinea, Carla Sospedra Salvador, Federico Moreira",
            "image": "alfuturo_ lp.jpg",
            "country": "Costa Rica, España\n",
            "countryEn": "Costa Rica, Spain, Uruguay",
            "productionCompanies": "Temporal Films\nEdna Cinema, SL\nLa Mayor Cine",
            "screenplay": "Paz Fábrega",
            "language": "Español",
            "languageEn": "Spanish",
            "genre": "Comedia dramática\nBiografía\nMadurez\nLGBT",
            "genreEn": "Dramatic comedy\r\nBiography\r\nComing of age\r\nLGBT",
            "duration": "93'",
            "totalBudget": "300 000 €",
            "synopsis": "Paz vive con sus dos hijos, Kai (3) y Matti (6), en un frágil ecosistema doméstico marcado por el cuidado, el agotamiento y la incertidumbre económica. Mientras busca trabajo, alquila una habitación de su casa a un flujo constante de inquilinos, cuyas llegadas y salidas reflejan la inestabilidad de su vida. Poco a poco Paz comienza a perder la noción del tiempo, olvidar pequeñas cosas, o incluso perder el equilibrio como cuidadora. Mientras su atención se fragmenta, Matti, dividido entre el deseo de ser visto y el de desaparecer, descubre una inquietante habilidad: puede aguantar la respiración durante largos periodos de tiempo. Rodada en la encrucijada entre el documental y la ficción, Al Futuro es el retrato de una madre y cineasta al límite, y donde la respiración de un niño se convierte en la medida del espacio que queda para respirar.",
            "synopsisEn": "Paz lives with her two children, Kai (3) and Matti (6), in a fragile domestic ecosystem marked by caregiving, exhaustion, and financial uncertainty. While looking for work, she rents out a room in her house to a constant stream of tenants, whose comings and goings reflect the instability of her daily life. Little by little, Paz begins to lose track of time, forget small things, or even lose her balance as a caregiver. As her attention fragments, Matti, torn between the desire to be seen and the desire to disappear, discovers a disturbing ability: he can hold his breath for long periods of time. Filmed at the crossroads between documentary and fiction, Al Futuro is the portrait of a mother and filmmaker pushed to her limits, where a child’s breath becomes the measure of the space left to breathe.",
            "biographyDirector": "Directora de cine, guionista y productora costarricense graduada de la UCR y la London FIlm School. Ha realizado también residencias en el Binger Filmlab y en la Cinefondation del Festival de Cannes. Su primer largometraje, “Agua fría de mar”, se estrenó en el Festival de Cine de Róterdam donde ganó el Premio VPRO Tiger, el galardón más prestigioso recibido por una película centroamericana en aquel momento. Ha sido miembro del jurado en festivales como Clermont-Ferrand, el Festival Internacional de Cine de Miami y el CRFIC, y ha participado en el comité de selección del World Cinema Fund.",
            "biographyDirectorEn": "A Costa Rican filmmaker, screenwriter, and producer, she graduated from the University of Costa Rica (UCR) and the London Film School. She has also completed residencies at the Binger Filmlab and the Cannes Film Festival’s Cinefondation. Her first feature film, “Agua fría de mar,” premiered at the Rotterdam Film Festival, where it won the VPRO Tiger Award, the most prestigious award received by a Central American film at that time. She has served on the jury at festivals such as Clermont-Ferrand, the Miami International Film Festival, and the CRFIC, and has been a member of the selection committee for the World Cinema Fund.",
            "biographyProducer": "Ha producido, entre otros títulos, «Mamífera», de Liliana Torres (SXSW, PÖFF, Varsovia, SSIFF, nominada a los Premios Gaudí); «¿Qué hicimos mal? », de Liliana Torres (Sevilla, PÖFF), «Correspondencias», de Carla Simón y Dominga Sotomayor (Zabaltegi, Visions du Reel, AFi Fest, Mar del Plata), o «El techo amarillo», de Isabel Coixet (SSIFF, IDFA y Hot Docs, Goya al Mejor Documental). En 2021 fundó su propia productora, Edna Cinema, y es alumni de EAVE Producers Workshop, Berlinale Talents y La Incubadora de la ECAM. Actualmente es una de las vicepresidentas de Dones Visuals.\n\n",
            "biographyProducerEn": "She has produced, among other titles, “Mamífera” by Liliana Torres (SXSW, PÖFF, Warsow, SSIFF, nominated to Gaudí Awards) “What went wrong? “by Liliana Torres (Seville, PÖFF), “Correspondences” by Carla Simón and Dominga Sotomayor (Zabaltegi, Visions du Reel, AFi Fest, Mar del Plata), and “The Yellow ceiling” by Isabel Coixet (SSIFF, IDFA and Hot Docs, Goya Best Documentary). She opened her own production company, Edna Cinema, in 2021, and is an alumni of EAVE Producers Workshop, Berlinale Talents and La Incubadora of ECAM. She is one of the vice presidents of Dones Visuals, a feminist filmakers association based in Catalonia.",
